<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Original Research</div>
    <h1>Cadence Design Systems (CDNS)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Cadence Design Systems — using actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Compiled by Gemini 3.1 · Updated March 18, 2026</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice !== null ? currentPrice.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(revCurrent / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">TTM/Current Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(fcfCurrent / 1000).toFixed(2)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${epsCurrent.toFixed(2)}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{((opIncomeCurrent / revCurrent) * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(2)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Cadence generated <strong>${fcfCurrent.toLocaleString()} million</strong> in free cash flow recently. This is real cash the business produces after paying for everything, including capital expenditures. It powers buybacks, debt paydowns, and acquisitions.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. Electronic Design Automation (EDA) software is absolutely essential for the design of complex semiconductors and AI chips. As complexity scales, reliance on Cadence's tools deepens, granting them immense pricing power and sticky revenues.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}% forever</strong> — roughly global GDP growth plus modest pricing power. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate). This captures all value from Year 6 to infinity.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100)}%</strong> — our required rate of return. This is the cost of equity (WACC) reflecting the 10Y Treasury (4.18%) plus a reasonable equity risk premium given CDNS's stable recurring revenue model and beta around 1.1.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${netCash.toLocaleString()}M) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Cadence forms an effective duopoly with Synopsys in the EDA market. The AI boom necessitates custom silicon and highly complex system-on-chips (SoCs). This complexity directly translates to sustained, high-margin, double-digit growth. 15% is aggressive but reflective of recent historical norms and their near-monopoly pricing power.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. With a beta near 1.1 and relatively low net debt, CDNS is less risky than many tech firms because their revenue is deeply ingrained in the semiconductor supply chain (recurring software licenses). 9.5% demands a strong return while acknowledging the software's indispensable nature.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth is ~3%. We add 0.5% for structural advantages: it is nearly impossible for a startup to displace CDNS/SNPS due to decades of IP and the catastrophic cost of switching EDA vendors. A 3.5% terminal growth rate assumes they maintain pricing power forever.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
